   VERSION=( "1.0.0" )
  CATEGORY="graphic"
 ATTRIBUTE="x11 new broken"
# may require libctl and libctl requires fortran and is currently marked broken
# if openexr_ctl requires a different CTL library than libctl
# then it aught to say where it can be downloaded from or the
# homepage, but it does not.
    SOURCE="openexr_ctl-$VERSION.tar.gz"
       URL="http://savannah.nongnu.org/download/openexr/"
  HOMEPAGE="http://www.openexr.com"
       REQ="libctl openexr"
  ESTIMATE="680"
      DESC="openexr_ctl provides a simplified OpenEXR interface to CTL

exrdpx is an initial version of a CTL-driven file converter
that translates DPX files into OpenEXR files and vice versa.
The conversion between the DPX and OpenEXR color spaces is
handled by CTL transforms.

exr_ctl_exr is an initial version of a program that can bake
the effect of a series of CTL transforms into the pixels of
an OpenEXR file."
